  "texts": [
    "They propose reporting the fraction of times a person (1) flips their initial, wrong judgment after seeing a correct model prediction, and (2) sticks with their initial, correct judgment after seeing a wrong model prediction.",
    "3 Wang and Yin (2021) aim for a similar procedure but allow scrolling to the model prediction while making the first guess, potentially influencing the standalone guess.",
    "Joshi et al. (2023)'s approach is similar to (1), but a person needs to flip their initial, wrong answer to the correct one upon seeing AI's explanation but not its prediction.",
    "4 This approach to measuring reliance where people make all final decisions with AI assistance is also how complementary human-AI team performance is typically measured.",
    "Human-AI teams should surpass the accuracy of both the AI alone and the human alone (Bansal et al., 2021), and explanations could provide a boost."
  ],
